Part Lead, Regional Sales Engineering, Samsung Air-Cond
Samsung Asia Pte Ltd

The Part Leader of Sales Engineering has a direct report to the RHQ AC Team Leader and will be responsible for in total 5 employees.

Main goals of the position
The main goal of the Part Leader of Sales Engineering is dual. On the one hand to increase, strengthen and professionalise the pre-sales in Southeast Asia & Oceania, and on the other hand to enhance the post-sales system and procedures of our air conditioning units.

The Position
Responsible for the development - and subsequently the execution - of a solid pre-sales & service strategy, and vision for the coming years;
Manage the Southeast Asian & Oceanian Training Centers : establishment and keeping them up to date, budget planning and control;
Aligning the training planning with the sales objectives and new product launching;
Enhance the builders/contractors network in the different Asian countries;
Monthly quality follow up and organising regular quality meetings with all local service teams;
Warranty and spare parts analysis;
If necessary, support the team in their operational activities; i.e. gathering specifications for the projects in pre-sales, accompany business development team in visiting prospects, etc.
Focus on close collaboration with the responsible country heads and also on the local pre sales and business development teams in the different countries;
Responsible for the yearly determination of the figures and targets per country (success ratio) and follow up.
Develop new business idea’s and models to support the company’s growth.
Improve contacts with the internal- and external relevant stakeholders;
Operational Excellence and KPI management;
Organisation of sharing knowledge conferences internally and externally.
Coach and lead the team.
The Profile
A minimum of a Master’s degree in Engineering preferably supplemented with a Commercial degree or an equivalent in working experience;
Minimum of 10 years’ experience in a senior international commercial development role within a technical/mechanical building engineering environment (network) with preferably HVAC knowledge;
Someone with a passion for engineering and is used to consultative selling, knows what is important and is technical achievable to create an ideal situation for the customer;
Someone who is used to work within complex matrix and international environments;
Has a strong network in the mechanical building branch and their clients in Asia;
Someone who has vision of the building/installation/HVAC market, is used to look ahead;
Who takes responsibility for his actions and knows how to enthuse his team and country heads;
A qualified candidate demonstrates strong leadership skills with an ability to convince the team and peers;
An organized, effective and positive people manager who has proven experience in coaching and managing multicultural teams;
Excellent communication skills are a necessity for this position. The position is a supervisory role and communication must be effective towards the team and also towards the international HQ in Korea and several local country organizations;
As a person he/she must be empathetic, persuasive, a real go-getter, confident, creative and a strong representative of the pre sales and business development team within the internal organization and also towards the external contact persons;
An excellent knowledge (speaking and writing) of the English language is mandatory and preferably any additional Asian language;
Actively travelling within Southeast Asia & Oceania (20%).

